        "title": "wrapping a gradle project with maven",
        "body": "<p>I want to wrap an existing gradle project (build.gradle) to also have a pom.xml file such that the following gradle tasks will be invoked when we invoke maven:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>'maven install' -> invoke 'gradle build'<\/li>\n<li>'maven clean' -> invoke 'gradle clean'<\/li>\n<li>'maven clean install -DskipTests' -> invoke 'gradle clean build -x tests'<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>So my question is:\nIs there a way to create a pom.xml that I can customize (and override) what 'install', 'clean' do? Additionally, Can I have access to the flags that were passed to maven so that I can rewrite them as the flags I want to pass to gradle?<\/p>\n\n<p>The ultimate goal is to include this project inside a larger multi project where all projects are maven based and we can automate everything based on maven commands.<\/p>\n",
